<item>
            <title>[LU-14040] Improve LNet Statistics</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14040</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Statistics are important when trying to understand the behaviour of a cluster&apos;s network. This epic will track:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;LNet message timing statistics:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;How long a message spends on the different queues&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;How long a message takes to complete&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Load/locking statistics
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The CPT architecture allows for processing load to be spread across the different CPTs, but there is no way to understand how heavily each CPT is being used
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;keep track of time taken for CPT specific operations; example MDUnlink/MDLookup&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
